LOS ANGELES/NEW YORK, April 6 (Reuters) - Following are the top 10 movies at North American box offices for the three days starting April 4, led by "Captain America: The Winter Soldier," according to studio estimates compiled by Reuters.

1  (*)  Captain America........................$  96.2 million 2  (1)  Noah...................................$  17.0 million 3  (2)  Divergent..............................$  13.0 million 4  (5)  God's Not Dead.........................$   7.7 million 5  (6)  The Grand Budapest Hotel...............$   6.3 million 6  (3)  Muppets Most Wanted....................$   6.3 million 7  (4)  Mr. Peabody & Sherman..................$   5.3 million 8  (7)  Sabotage...............................$   1.9 million 9  (8)  Need For Speed.........................$   1.8 million 10 (10) Non-Stop...............................$   1.8 million  Last week's rank in parentheses. (*) = new release